mpifx
------------------------------------------
The open source library MpiFx provides modern Fortran (Fortran 2003) wrappers
around routines of the MPI library to make their use as simple as possible.
Currently several data distribution routines are covered.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.6-1
  libgfortran5-13.4.0-1
  libmpifx-devel-1.6-1bl1
  libmpifx1-1.6-1bl1
  libopenmpifh40-4.1.6-1
  libopenmpiusef08_40-4.1.6-1
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.45.1-1
  cmake-4.2.1-1
  cygport-0.37.6-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  gcc-fortran-13.4.0-1
  libopenmpi-devel-4.1.6-1
  ninja-1.13.2-1
  python39-fypp-3.2-1bl1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/dftbplus/mpifx

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/dftbplus/mpifx/archive/refs/tags/1.6.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack mpifx-1.6-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./mpifx-1.6-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/mpifx-1.6-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/mpifx-1.6-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libmpifx1-1.6-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libmpifx-devel-1.6-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

